&gt;&gt; if there was somebody watching this interview right now and

00:04:56.310 --> 00:05:02.120
they're really intrigued about how biology and computer science and math,

00:05:02.120 --> 00:05:06.120
statistics work together in, in a particular job, what advice

00:05:06.120 --> 00:05:08.640
would you give them to, to study in school? What would

00:05:08.640 --> 00:05:11.820
you recommend that they do, and maybe where would you recommend

00:05:11.820 --> 00:05:16.300
that they seek you know, career advice or, or, or work

00:05:16.300 --> 00:05:21.780
&gt;&gt; Yeah. so as I said, I do believe there is needs for

00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:27.230
specialists or I do recommend they keep studying math and computer

00:05:27.230 --> 00:05:30.550
science and statistics a lot. But they still need

00:05:30.550 --> 00:05:34.340
to take some biology at the very least to figure

00:05:34.340 --> 00:05:36.260
what are the problems that we need to solve

00:05:36.260 --> 00:05:39.010
today in biology. And how to relate, you know it's

00:05:39.010 --> 00:05:42.612
not enough to get out of school and know

00:05:42.612 --> 00:05:46.190
a list of the ten fastest algorithms for each specific

00:05:46.190 --> 00:05:48.350
problem that you learn in school. You also need

